      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "FRONT MAN (7) placed two back then broke his maiden status by 1.75 lengths (19.21) at this track over 350m. Boxed wide here. Can make it two on the bounce. TIGGY BOODIE (6) doesn't have the best strike-rate but recent form is sound. Has been in the minors the last two runs, the latest finishing third (20.14) at Q Lakeside. Goes well out of this box with a win and two minor placings. Can feature again. TIBETAN BELLE (2) turned in a plain performance last time when fifth at Q Lakeside over 457m behind Terra Bella (26.15) in a Grade 6/MDN. Better than the latest run and deserves another chance. BLACK IS BACK (1) has ability and can feature with the right run after missing a cheque here most recently.",
